text.section:
In addition to the information that is required to be given under §§ 20-104 and 20-105 of this title, the driver of each vehicle involved in an accident under either of those sections shall also give the following information:
Name and address of the insurance carrier or other provider of security for the person giving the information;
Policy or other identifying number of the liability insurance or other security, if it is available;
Name and address of the local insurance producer or local office of the insurance carrier or other provider of security, if it is available; and
For a vehicle that is self-insured under the Administration's self-insurance program, evidence of self-insurance in the form required by the Administration.
